{{Game | Name=The Horus Heresy: Legions | Guid=3030-67983 | Deck=Space Marine Legions battle each other during The Horus Heresy, the brutal civil war that lead to Warhammer 40,000's grim dark future. | ReleaseDate=2018-03-15 | Characters= | Concepts=Concepts/Legions | Developers=Companies/Everguild | Franchises=Franchises/Warhammer_40_000 | Genres=Genres/Card_Game,Genres/Strategy | Locations= | Objects= | Platforms=Platforms/Android,Platforms/iPad,Platforms/iPhone,Platforms/Mac,Platforms/PC | Publishers= | Games=Games/Drakenlords_CCG_Card_Duels | Themes=Themes/Sci_Fi | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/37/378913/3013022-horusheresy_legions.jpg }}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"3013022-horusheresy_legions.jpg","path":"37\/378913\/","mime":"image\/jpeg","sizes":"square_medium,square_small,scale_medium,square_tiny,scale_super,scale_large,scale_small,square_mini,square_avatar,scale_avatar,scale_tiny,screen_kubrick,screen_medium","caption":null},"background":[]}' />
==Overview== The Horus Heresy: Legions is a digital card game set in the Warhammer 40,000 universe. The game uses key conflicts inspired by the Black Library novels as the basis for time-limited events. Players recreate these battles using decks consisting of a Warlord and 30 cards of troops and tactics in one-on-one turn based duels. These decks can either be constructed for ranked play or sealed for the time limited events.

